str2: Neuter of hostis as conjunction; demonstrative, that; causative, because.
Anointed One; the Messiah, the Christ. From chrio; Anointed One, i.e. The Messiah, an epithet of Jesus.

parse: Verb - Aorist Participle Passive - Nominative Masculine Singular
str2: (a) I wake, arouse, (b) I raise up. Probably akin to the base of agora; to waken, i.e. Rouse.
From out, out from among, from, suggesting from the interior outwards. A primary preposition denoting origin, from, out.
(a) adj: dead, lifeless, subject to death, mortal, (b) noun: a dead body, a corpse. From an apparently primary nekus; dead.

str2: To be dying, be about to die, wither, decay. From apo and thnesko; to die off.
Death, physical or spiritual. From thnesko; death.
No longer, no more. Also ouk eti from ou and eti; not yet, no longer.

parse: Verb - Present Indicative Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: To have authority, rule over. From kurios; to rule.

parse: Personal / Possessive Pronoun - Genitive Masculine 3rd Person Singular
str2: He, she, it, they, them, same. From the particle au; the reflexive pronoun self, used of the third person, and of the other persons.
